Description: Shoulder sherd of East Greek (North Ionian?) pottery closed vessel, probably an oenochoe; pale brown clay with silver mica; worn on the outside; inscription cut on exterior.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Sanctuary of Apollo (Naukratis), temenos (said to be)
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GG.957)
